--- OLLAMA ERROR ANALYSIS ---
**Error Analysis:**
The build failed during RPM's post-install verification because **10 files** were installed to the `BUILDROOT` but are not listed in the `%files` section. This triggers a fatal `Installed (but unpackaged) file(s) found` error, which blocks package creation. The missing files consist of one utility binary (`gawkbug`) and documentation (info figures and man pages).

**Required Fix:**
Add the following three lines to your `%files` section. These explicitly list the standalone debugger and use standard RPM macros to capture all info/figure and man1 files without hardcoding paths.

```diff
@@ -... +... @@
 %doc AUTHORS NEWS README THANKS
+# Add missing installed files detected by rpmlint
+%{_bindir}/gawkbug
+%{_infodir}/*
+%{_mandir}/man1/*
```

**Why this works:**
- `%{_bindir}/gawkbug` packages the exact binary listed in `/usr/bin/`.
- `%{_infodir}/*` captures all 7 `.png` documentation figures installed to `/usr/share/info/`.
- `%{_mandir}/man1/*` captures `gawkbug.1.gz` and `pm-gawk.1.gz` installed to `/usr/share/man/man1/`.

Apply this diff, then retry the build. No interactive investigation or dependency changes are required.
